dct_alternative_sm: Kue Shan Is. to the Yangtze Kiang including Chusan Archipelago
dct_description_sm: From Surveys by Commr. W.U. Moore, R.N., H.M.S. 'Rambler," 1887, and Commanders W.U. Moore and L.S. Dawson R.N., H.M.S. 'Rambler,' 1888-1890, and Captain W.U. Moore R.N., H.M.S. 'Penguin,' 1892. Yangtze Kiang from Chinese Maritime Customs Charts to 1928, with corrections to 1937 ; published at the Admiralty 13th, Augt. 1883, under the Superintendence of Captain Sir Frederick J. Evans. R.N.: K.C.B.: F.R.S. Hydrographer ; Sold by J.D. Potter, Agent for the sale of the Admiralty Charts ; Reproduced by the U.S. Hydrographic Office from British Admiralty Chart with the permission of the Controller, H.M. Stationery Office and Hydrographer of the Royal Navy.
Depths shown by soundings; relief by hachures and spot heights.
Tidal information table, tidal streams note.
Shows low water areas, islands, drainage, lights, vegetation/wetlands, towns, roads, railroads.
"[U.S. Hydrographic Office] Emergency reproduction of B.A. Chart _ Jan. 1937; June 1938; Jan.1942"
